sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Customer
    participant UI as Mobile/Web App
    participant BFF as Web/Mobile BFF
    participant Orch as Onboarding Orchestrator
    participant CoreAdapter as Account Creation Service
    participant Kafka as Event Backbone
    participant CoreBank as Core Banking
    participant Notif as Notification Service

    Note over Orch, Kafka: 1. Trigger Account Creation
    Orch->>CoreAdapter: Request account creation
    CoreAdapter->>Kafka: Publish account.requested (topic-account-events)
    CoreAdapter-->>Orch: 202 Accepted (ACCOUNT_CREATION_PENDING)

    Note over Customer, Orch: 2. UI Polling & Graceful Degradation
    loop UI Polling (Every 3-5s)
        UI->>BFF: GET /onboarding/{sessionId}/status
        BFF->>Orch: Route Request
        Orch-->>UI: 200 OK (Status: ACCOUNT_CREATION_PENDING)
        Note over Customer, UI: UI shows: "We’re finalising your new account. You’ll get a message shortly"
    end

    Note over Kafka, CoreBank: 3. Delayed Background Processing
    Note right of CoreBank: Core system is overwhelmed. It consumes the event slowly.
    Kafka->>CoreBank: Consume account.requested (delayed)
    CoreBank->>Kafka: Publish account.opened (topic-account-events)

    Note over Kafka, Notif: 4. Event Publication & Choreography
    par Orchestrator State Update
        Kafka->>Orch: Consume account.opened
        Note over Orch: Update session status to COMPLETED
        Orch->>Kafka: Publish onboarding.status.changed (topic-onboarding-events)
    and Asynchronous Notifications
        Kafka->>Notif: Consume onboarding.status.changed
        Notif-->>Customer: Send Welcome Email/SMS
    end